CLIENTHELP1="Join a client to the domain"
CLIENTHELP2="Windows client computers are joined to the domain in the same way as for a windows network. "
CLIENTHELP2b="The username required to do this is Administrator. The password will be the system password that you chose earlier."
CLIENTHELP2c="You can also join client computers to the domain using any accounts that are members of the itadmin group."
CLIENTHELP3="Once you have successfully joined a client you can test it with the new user that you have just created."
CLIENTHELP4="Karoshi linux clients can be joined to the domain using the icons provided on the desktop for the local administrator user account on the linux client."
CUSTOMISEPROFILESMSG="Profiles"
PROFILEHELP1="By default windows clients use mandatory profiles."
PROFILEHELP1b="New profiles are created using the profileuser account."
PROFILEHELP2="The profileuser account uses a roaming profile that you can customise. "
PROFILEHELP2b="Copy the profileuser profile by right clicking on My Computer and using the profile management tools."
PROFILEHELP2c="It is essential that the permissions are changed on the profile to allow all users to use it."
PROFILEHELP3="The copied profile can be zipped up and uploaded to the web management."
PROFILEHELP4="The Karoshi Linux clients download an updated skel from the main server each time that the client is booted. "
PROFILEHELP4b="Users logging onto the client then use the skel from the local machines."
